<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41001b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41001b">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41001b"> 1(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> heirs male of / his body</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">With the exception, however, of certain ancient grants, peerages are created by letters patent and descend in succession to descendants of the original peer in the manner expressly limited by such letters. In general, the grant is to the original peer &ldquo;and the <mark>heirs male of his body</mark>,&rdquo; that is only to his sons and to male descendants descended from him only through males. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
